Teltoli smiled, if a bit watery, and suddenly grinned. "You sound so 
much like a mother, you know that? Oh, and don't worry, I definatly 
know how you feel at being left alone. Or, maybe I don't, because I 
kinda had a good life. Or maybe.." She stopped babbling in her 
relief, and winced.

With a groan Teltoli noticed Instrat again, and transformed into her 
Bot Mode. Mostly black, her armour gave her a good advantage in 
darkness, but the silver 'gloves' and ankle rings gleamed dully in 
the lightening. Having no real weapons in her beast mode, apart from 
fangs and claws, she always preferred bot for a fight. 

Her right hand hovered over the gun in her leg sheath, ready in case 
the new bot tried anything.
